The paper deals with information theory and its mathematical foundations, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses properties of directed information, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of probability measures on abstract spaces suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the analysis of extremum problems related to capacity of channels and rate distortion suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
